<article>
    <h1>RE&#xAD;FRESH&#xAD;ING LYCHEE-IN&#xAD;FUSED SORBET</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20200814/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-08-14"><time>2020-08-14</time></a>
        - <span>LIFE HAPPENINGS</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>I am on a Na­tional Day high this month and go­ing all out for themed food and drink.</p>
    <p>The lo­cal mas­ter fran­chise of Aus­tralia’s gelato brand Ge­latis­simo pays trib­ute to Sin­ga­pore with a “Lychee Go, Sin­ga­pore” sorbet series (left).</p>
    <p>Lychee was picked for its red and white colours.</p>
    <p>Apart from the orig­i­nal lychee flavour, the fruit is also in­fused with four other flavours for the sorbet: straw­berry, wa­ter­melon, blood or­ange and green ap­ple. They come as a set, priced at $33 for five 100ml tubs (one flavour each).</p>
    <p>I like the re­fresh­ing wa­ter­melon, straw­berry and blood or­ange flavours – they are good for a sweet treat in the heat.</p>
    <p>A bonus of the sorbet set is that it comes with a set of Sin­ga­porethemed nail wraps (worth $15) by pop­u­lar home-grown brand Nodspark. De­signs in­clude Hello Mer­lion, Ca­ble Car, Lo­cal Ke­baya, Au­tumn Leaves and Dainty Fo­liage.</p>
    <p>WHERE: Ge­latis­simo’s out­lets at 01-01 Shaw House, 350 Or­chard Road; 01-14 Sin­ga­pore Flyer, 30 Raf­fles Av­enue; and Sen­tosa, 01-K8 Beach Sta­tion, 50 Beach View</p>
    <p>MRT: Or­chard/Prom­e­nade/ Har­bourFront WHEN: Till Aug 31</p>
    <p>TEL: 9871-6487 INFO: Or­der one day in ad­vance at ge­latis­simo.od­dle.me; min­i­mum or­der of $40 for free is­land­wide de­liv­ery or pay $10 de­liv­ery charge</p>

